    <note>Lu(5) Xuanji [33756] Pinghu XZ (1629), pp. 641-643 cites a man of this name as a Song Assistant Military councillor of state and founder of the a and b branches of the Pinghu Wujun Lu(5). We can find no such person, certainly nobody who held this office. My guess is that the man is Lu(5) Youliang [1291] and the office is a minor office in the Bureau of military affairs.</note>
